Despite these potential biases, the compilation of sites in our database represents an excep-
tionally high-quality record available for analysing human occupation during the Solutrean,
Magdalenian and Iberomaurusian in the Western Mediterranean. Due to this, we regard the
results obtained fromthe following analyses as relatively robust and the data adequate to infer
certain properties of prehistoric settlement and land use dynamics.
